Active high. Provides a capability to defer incoming configuration requests until initialization is complete. When this bit is set, PCIe controller completes incoming configuration requests with a Configuration Request Retry Status. Other incoming requests complete with unsupported request status. 1 1 0x0 R/W HOT_RESET DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_WIDTH DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_MSB DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_LSB DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_RANGE DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_RESET DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_FIELD_MASK DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_GET DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_HOT_RESET_SET DWC_pcie_subsystem_custom.csr 2413 Hot Reset. A rising edge causes a hot reset. PCIe subsystem generates a one-cycle pulse for app_init_rst to PCIe controller in core_clk domain on this rising edge of this register. To trigger a hot reset, you can write 1 to this bit. This read value of this bit is always 0. 2 2 0x0 W RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_WIDTH DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_MSB DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_LSB DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_RANGE DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_RESET DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_FIELD_MASK DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_GET DWC_PCIE_SUBSYSTEM_CUSTOM_APB_SLAVE_SUBSYSTEM_PE1_GEN_CTRL_3_RAS_DES_SD_HOLD_LTSSM_SET DWC_pcie_subsystem_custom.csr 2421 Hold and release LTSSM.
